      "project_abstract": "The Eastside Neighborhood Revitalization Initiative will address deteriorating housing conditions and limited economic opportunity in Springfield's Eastside district. The project will rehabilitate 15 owner-occupied homes, establish a micro-enterprise incubator providing business training and seed grants to 25 residents, and create a community resource center offering workforce development programs. Over 24 months, the initiative expects to serve 200 low-income households, generate 40 new jobs, and leverage $500,000 in private matching investment.",
